\lim_{n\to\infty} |a_n - a_{n+1}|=0
(a_n)
\sin(2\pi n)
a_n:=1+\frac{1}{2}+...+\frac{1}{n}
\,|a_{n+1}-a_n|=\frac{1}{n+1}\xrightarrow [n\to\infty]{}0\,
a_n=\sqrt{n}
\bigl\{0,{1\over2},1,{2\over3},{1\over3},0,{1\over4},{2\over4},{3\over4},1,{4\over5},\ldots\bigr\}
a_n=\ln(n)
\lim_{n\to \infty } |\ln(n)-\ln(n+1)| = \lim_{n\to \infty } \left|\ln\left(\frac{n}{n+1}\right)\right| = 0 \,.
\lim_{n\to \infty } \ln(n) =\infty\,. 
